{
  "number": 2160,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2160",
  "title": "RefinementListWidgetOptions.showMore should conditionally render",
  "body": "**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\n`RefinementListWidgetOptions.showMore` template always renders, regardless of # of facets or `RefinementListWidgetOptions.limit`.\r\n\r\nIt should only render when the requested # of facets is greater than `RefinementListWidgetOptions.limit` (v1 behavior), or some sort of disabled class should be applied so it can be hidden with CSS.\r\n\r\nhttps://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/refinementList.html#struct-RefinementListWidgetOptions-showMore\r\n\r\nLooks like it was brought up here, but I'm not seeing it fixed in `v2.0.0-beta.2`: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/1455.\r\n\r\nThis works as expected in v1. The show more block isn't rendered at all if it is not applicable.\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\n`v2.0.0-beta.2`",
